doc.previous: In November 2004, CMP Media applied to the USPTO for a service mark on the use of the term "WEB 2.0" for live events.[79] On the basis of this application, CMP Media sent a cease-and-desist demand to the Irish non-profit organization IT@Cork on May 24, 2006,[80] but retracted it two days later.[81] The "WEB 2.0" service mark registration passed final PTO Examining Attorney review on May 10, 2006, and was registered on June 27, 2006.[79] The European Union application (which would confer unambiguous status in Ireland)[82] was declined on May 23, 2007.
